product_name: FENTY BEAUTY by RihannaEaze Drop Lightweight Blurring Skin Tint
summary: SummaryHighlightsCruelty FreeA lightweight, easy-to-apply, light to medium coverage skin tint that instantly evens out your complexion and gives a flattering blurred effect. With hydrating QuickBlur complex, its perfect for a no-makeup makeup look, or for when you want to look effortlessly put together.

reviews.headline: Purrfect
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] I got this as a free sample but I've already bought it a few times before because it's one of my favorite skin tints. The shade match (11)is perfect for my skin and it blends in so easily. It gives me a smooth blurred look while still feeling really lightweight and natural. It's become one of those products I keep going back to because it always works for me.

reviews.headline: Holy Grail Skin Tint
reviews.comments:
I received this product in exchange for my honest review. I love this blurring skin tint, it blends effortlessly into my skin with zero streaks or patchy "tan" lines. It gives me that perfect sun-kissed glow without looking overdone. A little goes a long way, seriously, one drop is enough for full coverage, and the bottle seems to last forever!
The dispenser is genius â€” it gives just the right amount every time, so there's no mess or waste. The texture is light and breathable, yet it smooths and softens my skin like a dream. It doesn't feel heavy at all, and it stays put all day without needing touch-ups. If you're looking for that "your skin but better" glow, this is it. Total staple in my routine!

reviews.headline: I love it
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] This foundation makes my skin so glowy and vibrant. I love how it moisturizes and sits on my skin. I feel like it looks great with a little powder in my t zone and oily spots.

faceoff_positive.comments:
[I received this product in exchange for my honest review] I was very impressed with Fenty Beauty "Eaze Drop" Blurring Skin Tint. It has a consistency slightly thicker than water, so I really didn't think this would be enough coverage for me due to my sun spots and discoloration.
I've always been more into heavy coverage foundation over skin tints, tinted moisturizers, and BB creams. The only issue I've begun to notice is that as I age, sometimes heavier coverage foundations settle into my wrinkles and make them stand out more (no bueno). Well, imagine my surprise when I put this on, and it actually covered many of my skin imperfections! With such a light fluid, I really don't know how they achieved this, but it works! You can see for yourself in the photo I attached. The left pic is wearing no foundation at all. On the right, I am wearing the Fenty Eaze Drop Blurring Skin Tint in shade #6. I have no other make-up on my skin (I did put some sunscreen on underneath, though). In my opinion, my skin looks almost glowing, and it covered my sun spots and discoloration better than any foundation I have in my rotation. Also, the photos were taken with my iPhone in the exact same place, right by my window. 
I was really happy with the look, but for fun, I wanted to see if my boyfriend noticed anything (they rarely notice if you get your hair colored, so I was not actually expecting him to notice). I did half my face in the Skin Tint and left the other side sans make-up. I went up to him and said, "Which side of my face looks best?" Without hesitation, he immediately pointed to the side that had the Fenty Eaze Drop Blurring Skin Tint on it! WOW!

A Few Other Points:
 * I am pretty picky about how foundation feels when I wear it, and how it feels and looks several hours in. This passed those tests. It felt light and natural on my skin even after several hours.
 * Even though I'm middle-aged, I still get breakouts (yay for me, right!?). This tint did not make me break out! Even my shower water breaks me out, so this is an accomplishment for sure.

Now the Cons:
 * Since I had sunscreen on underneath, I found that if I blended too much, the two would start to pill. I think I just rubbed too much. So be sure to blend lightly and not too much if you're wearing anything underneath it. This could also be the sunscreen, so take this with a grain of salt. The pilling was very minor as well.
 * The bottle holds 1.08 fl oz. This seems a bit small to me. That said, you do not need a lot of product (way less than regular foundation), plus it's a convenient size for travel.

Overall, this was a complete win in my book, and I'll be using this all the time!
faceoff_positive.headline: Great Coverage for a Skin Tint! It Really Works!

faceoff_negative.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] I have really mixed feelings about this product. It's the weirdest skin tent I've ever tried. So to start off at first, it felt really nice on my skin and as you see in the picture, it literally made my skin look airbrushed. I have a lot of hyper pigmentation and some acne scars and to be a skin tint. It really did fill in those imperfections very nicely. The shade was perfect for me. I have a medium skin tone with an olive undertone. However, I noticed within two hours my skin started to look very orange and blotchy. I have really dry skin and rarely ever use setting powder, but I decided the next time I wore it that I would try to do setting powder to see if this would prevent the blotchiness and I seen no difference. The texture of this is very weird. It comes out very watery, but if you don't use a light hand, it can go on very heavy. I cannot say that I would fully recommend it to somebody if they have a lot of hyperpigmentation and they are looking for a solid full coverage skin tint, but I think if you have normal skin type with minor imperfections, this would be a good product. I did not notice any breakouts or anything after using this and I do have sensitive skin so I did appreciate that. I just don't know if it's a skin tent that I will be reaching for because as I said, my skin never looked better, but then an hour later my skin looked horrible.
faceoff_negative.headline: Mixed feelings
